{\ O (spread)}

1995
02:21:36,376 --> 02:21:39,658
<i>(Yellow...)</i>
{\ O (spread)}

1996
02:21:39,658 --> 02:21:42,941
<i>Over...</i>
{\ O (spread)}

1997
02:21:42,941 --> 02:21:46,223
<i>(Over!)</i>
{\ O (spread)}

1998
02:21:46,223 --> 02:21:49,505
<i>Sunlight yellow, sunlight yellow</i>
{\ O (spread)}

1999
02:21:49,505 --> 02:21:52,788
<i>Overdrive!!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2000
02:21:52,788 --> 02:21:56,070
The ripple of the sun! Dio!
{\ O (spread)}

2001
02:21:56,070 --> 02:21:59,352
This is the power
that will defeat you!
{\ O (spread)}

2002
02:21:59,352 --> 02:22:02,635
Dio Brando?
{\ O (spread)}

2003
02:22:02,635 --> 02:22:05,917
Yeah?
{\ O (spread)}

2004
02:22:09,200 --> 02:22:11,200
I don’t know you, but...
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Don't do it}

2005
02:22:11,200 --> 02:22:15,888
Let me say this to the Stone
Mask that awakened your brain:
{\ O (spread)}

2006
02:22:15,888 --> 02:22:20,577
Finally, we meet.
{\ O (spread)}

2007
02:22:20,577 --> 02:22:25,266
Don’t get carried away!
{\ O (spread)}

2008
02:22:25,266 --> 02:22:29,955
Perhaps you can heal this
wound in my stomach, JoJo.
{\ O (spread)}

2009
02:22:29,955 --> 02:22:34,644
You’re the one who put it there!
{\ O (spread)}

2010
02:22:34,644 --> 02:22:39,333
Then I’ll be completely healed from
the damage you dealt me in that fire.
{\ O (spread)}

2011
02:22:39,333 --> 02:22:44,022
I’ll be using your lives...
{\ O (spread)}

2012
02:22:44,022 --> 02:22:48,711
To purge this wound!
{\ O (spread)}

2013
02:22:48,711 --> 02:22:53,400
You bastard!
{\ O (spread)}

2014
02:22:53,400 --> 02:22:58,088
Just how many lives did you
extinguish to heal that wound?
{\ O (spread)}

2015
02:22:58,088 --> 02:23:02,777
Do you remember how many slices of
bread you’ve eaten in your lifetime?
{\ O (spread)}

2016
02:23:02,777 --> 02:23:07,466
I’ll make you submit!
{\ O (spread)}

2017
02:23:07,466 --> 02:23:12,155
By the ripple of the sun!
{\ O (spread)}

2018
02:23:12,155 --> 02:23:16,844
Pow!
{\ O (spread)}

2019
02:23:16,844 --> 02:23:21,533
Utterly pathetic!
{\ O (spread)}

2020
02:23:21,533 --> 02:23:26,222
It’s freezing?!
{\ O (spread)}

2021
02:23:26,222 --> 02:23:30,911
I guessed that this energy of yours
is related to the flow of your blood!
{\ O (spread)}

2022
02:23:30,911 --> 02:23:35,600
I am able to control my own body at will.
{\ O (spread)}

2023
02:23:35,600 --> 02:23:40,288
If I freeze up all of your veins,
{\ O (spread)}

2024
02:23:40,288 --> 02:23:44,977
Then you won’t be able to use that power!
{\ O (spread)}

2025
02:23:44,977 --> 02:23:49,666
I can’t—I can’t catch my breath!
{\ O (spread)}

2026
02:23:49,666 --> 02:23:54,355
Mr. Zeppeli!
{\ O (spread)}

2027
02:23:54,355 --> 02:23:59,044
Useless, useless, useless, useless!
{\ O (spread)}

2028
02:23:59,044 --> 02:24:03,733
Breathing techniques? Ripple?
{\ O (spread)}

2029
02:24:03,733 --> 02:24:08,422
If you’re going to be
blowing all this hot air,
{\ O (spread)}

2030
02:24:08,422 --> 02:24:13,111
You ought to use it to
play me a little fanfare!
{\ O (spread)}

2031
02:24:13,111 --> 02:24:17,800
Looks like your companions
are just as weak as you.
{\ O (spread)}

2032
02:24:17,800 --> 02:24:22,488
JOJO: What did you say?
DIO: Companions...
{\ O (spread)}

2033
02:24:22,488 --> 02:24:27,177
That’s right. Do you remember?
{\ O (spread)}

2034
02:24:27,177 --> 02:24:31,866
The story of the knights
your father told us that day?
{\ O (spread)}

2035
02:24:31,866 --> 02:24:36,555
What?
{\ O (spread)}

2036
02:24:36,555 --> 02:24:41,244
The tragic queen who was sentenced
to beheading by Elizabeth the First,
{\ O (spread)}

2037
02:24:41,244 --> 02:24:45,933
After a failed assassination
plot in the 1600s...
{\ O (spread)}

2038
02:24:45,933 --> 02:24:50,622
Mary Stuart!
{\ O (spread)}

2039
02:24:50,622 --> 02:24:55,311
It was about the ones who served her!
{\ O (spread)}

2040
02:24:52,200 --> 02:24:53,200
Yes!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Yes.}

2041
02:24:53,200 --> 02:24:58,000
We listened to it together, didn’t we?!
{\ O (spread)}

2042
02:24:58,000 --> 02:25:02,800
JoJo, Dio!
{\ O (spread)}

2043
02:25:00,000 --> 02:25:02,000
The story of those two proud knights...
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: The story of the knight that my parents told}

2044
02:25:02,000 --> 02:24:52,199
Father told us...
{\ O (spread)}

2045
02:25:02,800 --> 02:25:07,600
I will regale you with
a tale of two knights,
{\ O (spread)}

2046
02:25:07,600 --> 02:25:12,400
Which has been passed down for
generations in our great England.
{\ O (spread)}

2047
02:25:12,400 --> 02:25:17,200
Those who lived with a gentleman’s spirit—
{\ O (spread)}

2048
02:25:22,000 --> 02:25:25,000
This is a story of knightly pride!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: It's the story of a proud knight.}

2049
02:25:25,000 --> 02:25:29,435
<i>Long ago, 300 years before today</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2050
02:25:29,435 --> 02:25:33,871
<i>Two queens battled for the throne</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2051
02:25:33,871 --> 02:25:38,306
<i>One was Queen Elizabeth the First</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2052
02:25:38,306 --> 02:25:42,742
<i>And the other, the beautiful Mary Stuart</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2053
02:25:42,742 --> 02:25:47,178
<i>Two legendary heroes came forward,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2054
02:25:47,178 --> 02:25:51,613
<i>Offering up their swords to serve Mary</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2055
02:25:51,613 --> 02:25:56,049
<i>Tarkus’s strength cleaved
through rocks like butter</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2056
02:25:56,049 --> 02:26:00,485
<i>Bruford, with his skill and spirit,
cut down foes like a phantom</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2057
02:26:00,485 --> 02:26:04,920
<i>Without any family, the
two honed their powers</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2058
02:26:04,920 --> 02:26:09,356
<i>While wishing for a nest to rest in</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2059
02:26:09,356 --> 02:26:13,792
<i>After finding peace in Mary’s affections,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2060
02:26:13,792 --> 02:26:18,227
<i>They swore their loyalty to her</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2061
02:26:18,227 --> 02:26:22,663
But one day, Elizabeth
accused their master, Mary,
{\ O (spread)}

2062
02:26:22,663 --> 02:26:27,099
Of murdering her husband,
and she was captured.
{\ O (spread)}

2063
02:26:27,099 --> 02:26:31,534
<i>The two heroes would not rest</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2064
02:26:31,534 --> 02:26:35,970
<i>When it came to saving their Mary</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2065
02:26:35,970 --> 02:26:40,406
<i>In order to stop those two heroes,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2066
02:26:40,406 --> 02:26:44,841
<i>Elizabeth made an appeal:</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2067
02:26:44,841 --> 02:26:49,277
<i>“You two, surrender at once!”</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2068
02:26:49,277 --> 02:26:53,713
<i>“And I will spare your master’s life!”</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2069
02:26:53,713 --> 02:26:58,148
<i>This, we cannot refuse</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2070
02:26:58,148 --> 02:27:02,584
<i>In this, we hold no regrets</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2071
02:27:02,584 --> 02:27:07,020
<i>For our queen is our life!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2072
02:27:07,020 --> 02:27:11,455
But in the moment they
were to be executed—
{\ O (spread)}

2073
02:27:11,455 --> 02:27:15,891
I’ll give you a little souvenir
before your trip to Hell!
{\ O (spread)}

2074
02:27:15,891 --> 02:27:20,326
Your master isn’t being held in the tower.
{\ O (spread)}

2075
02:27:20,326 --> 02:27:24,762
I cut off her head myself just yesterday!
{\ O (spread)}

2076
02:27:24,762 --> 02:27:29,198
Look at her lying over
there like a piece of rubbish!
{\ O (spread)}

2077
02:27:29,198 --> 02:27:33,633
After all, if she was left alive,
we’d risk a rebellion!
{\ O (spread)}

2078
02:27:33,633 --> 02:27:38,069
<i>You’ve betrayed us, Elizabeth</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2079
02:27:38,069 --> 02:27:42,505
<i>We curse you with our grudge!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2080
02:27:42,505 --> 02:27:46,940
<i>We curse you for all eternity!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2081
02:27:46,940 --> 02:27:51,376
<i>Stiff with rage, Tarkus’s
muscles were like iron</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2082
02:27:51,376 --> 02:27:55,812
<i>They couldn’t cut through his neck!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2083
02:27:55,812 --> 02:28:00,247
<i>Bruford, filled with regret,
ensnared them with his hair</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2084
02:28:00,247 --> 02:28:04,683
<i>As though it were alive!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2085
02:28:04,683 --> 02:28:09,119
<i>And that is the story,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2086
02:28:09,119 --> 02:28:13,554
<i>Of those knights who lived
according to their hearts</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2087
02:28:13,554 --> 02:28:17,990
<i>Until the very end!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2088
02:28:17,990 --> 02:28:22,426
Such blind devotion—
it gives me goosebumps!
{\ O (spread)}

2089
02:28:22,426 --> 02:28:26,861
Oh, what loyal hearts!
{\ O (spread)}

2090
02:28:26,861 --> 02:28:31,297
But those two should
have done a better job!
{\ O (spread)}

2091
02:28:31,297 --> 02:28:35,733
In the end, they couldn’t do
anything from down in the mud.
{\ O (spread)}

2092
02:28:35,733 --> 02:28:40,168
The only thing to call
their deaths is useless!
{\ O (spread)}

2093
02:28:40,168 --> 02:28:44,604
It might be as you say, however—
{\ O (spread)}

2094
02:28:44,604 --> 02:28:49,039
There is nothing that is without meaning.
{\ O (spread)}

2095
02:28:49,039 --> 02:28:53,475
The same can be said about the
fact that you came here to this house.
{\ O (spread)}

2096
02:28:53,475 --> 02:28:57,911
Everything is connected!
{\ O (spread)}

2097
02:28:57,911 --> 02:29:02,346
I want to believe that they
kept on looking at the stars!
{\ O (spread)}

2098
02:29:02,346 --> 02:29:06,782
<i>All people live in a prison called fate</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2099
02:29:06,782 --> 02:29:11,218
<i>Reaching out through those bars,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2100
02:29:11,218 --> 02:29:15,653
<i>Do they see the stars? Or the mud?</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2101
02:29:15,653 --> 02:29:20,089
<i>Either one—</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2102
02:29:20,089 --> 02:29:24,525
<i>JoJo</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2103
02:29:24,525 --> 02:29:28,960
<i>Dio</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2104
02:29:28,960 --> 02:29:33,396
<i>Could be said to be correct!</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2105
02:29:33,396 --> 02:29:37,832
I turned those two
{\ O (spread)}

2106
02:29:37,832 --> 02:29:42,267
Into vengeful revenants that
would send even the devil running!
{\ O (spread)}

2107
02:29:42,267 --> 02:29:46,703
Even history bends before me!
{\ O (spread)}

2108
02:29:46,703 --> 02:29:51,139
It can’t be!
{\ O (spread)}

2109
02:29:51,139 --> 02:29:55,574
Such grotesque forms!
{\ O (spread)}

2110
02:29:55,574 --> 02:30:00,010
It’s the perfect form for
taking their revenge!
{\ O (spread)}

2111
02:30:00,010 --> 02:30:04,446
Don’t you think so?
{\ O (spread)}

2112
02:30:04,446 --> 02:30:08,881
Kill them all!
{\ O (spread)}

2113
02:30:08,881 --> 02:30:13,317
Continue from where
you left off on that day!
{\ O (spread)}

2114
02:30:13,317 --> 02:30:17,753
Tarkus!
{\ O (spread)}

2115
02:30:17,753 --> 02:30:22,188
Bruford!
{\ O (spread)}

2116
02:30:22,188 --> 02:30:26,624
Play me a fanfare with their screams!
{\ O (spread)}

2117
02:30:31,060 --> 02:30:33,060
Our grudge!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: To avenge a grudge}

2118
02:30:33,060 --> 02:30:34,393
Our pride!
{\ O (spread)}

2119
02:30:34,393 --> 02:30:35,726
Great Dark Knight Bruford!
{\ O (spread)}

2120
02:30:37,060 --> 02:30:39,060
And you, Tarkus!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Don't you think so?}

2121
02:30:39,060 --> 02:30:42,202
The way you feel—
{\ O (spread)}

2122
02:30:42,202 --> 02:30:45,345
Your pride, your resentment.
{\ O (spread)}

2123
02:30:45,060 --> 02:30:47,060
Tarkus!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Tarkus}

2124
02:30:45,345 --> 02:30:48,488
I can’t even imagine it!
{\ O (spread)}

2125
02:30:47,060 --> 02:30:52,277
I won’t let you interfere!
{\ O (spread)}

2126
02:30:48,488 --> 02:30:51,631
But I also bear my own burdens!
{\ O (spread)}

2127
02:30:51,631 --> 02:30:54,774
I’m gonna be the one to eat ‘em!
{\ O (spread)}

2128
02:30:52,277 --> 02:30:57,494
<i>A wedge driven into the
wasteland of my memory</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2129
02:30:54,774 --> 02:30:57,917
I’ll savour every bit of his cartilage!
{\ O (spread)}

2130
02:30:57,060 --> 02:30:59,060
My master—I, Bruford,
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Pride, the great wrestler Bruford}

2131
02:30:57,494 --> 02:31:02,712
<i>At dawn, a blood-red sun
rose over the Atlantic Ocean</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2132
02:30:59,060 --> 02:30:45,059
Would like to be the one to bring
an end to this brave man’s life!
{\ O (spread)}

2133
02:30:59,061 --> 02:30:45,059
Alright, go ahead!
{\ O (spread)}

2134
02:30:59,063 --> 02:30:45,059
We’ll duel as knights!
{\ O (spread)}

2135
02:30:59,064 --> 02:30:45,059
Run away, you two!
{\ O (spread)}

2136
02:30:59,066 --> 02:30:45,059
Mr. Joestar!
{\ O (spread)}

2137
02:31:01,060 --> 02:31:03,060
That man’s pride...
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Your thoughts and pride}

2138
02:31:02,712 --> 02:31:07,929
Old man!
{\ O (spread)}

2139
02:31:03,060 --> 02:30:57,059
I will stand to meet it, as a knight!
{\ O (spread)}

2140
02:31:07,929 --> 02:31:13,146
Don’t come any closer!
{\ O (spread)}

2141
02:31:13,146 --> 02:31:18,364
Damn it...
{\ O (spread)}

2142
02:31:18,364 --> 02:31:23,581
Fucking hell!
{\ O (spread)}

2143
02:31:23,581 --> 02:31:28,799
<i>There’s nothing I can do,
I’m a mere spectator</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2144
02:31:28,799 --> 02:31:34,016
<i>I’ve got nothing, I’m powerless</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2145
02:31:34,016 --> 02:31:39,233
<i>Come on, get real,
even at a time like this?</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2146
02:31:39,233 --> 02:31:44,451
<i>Even if I give up, the pain
will just be for another day</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2147
02:31:44,451 --> 02:31:49,668
<i>And tomorrow, yes tomorrow,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2148
02:31:49,668 --> 02:31:54,886
<i>I’ll still be over here crying like a loser</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2149
02:31:54,886 --> 02:32:00,103
Honourable knight,
{\ O (spread)}

2150
02:32:00,103 --> 02:32:05,320
Is revenge your answer?
{\ O (spread)}

2151
02:32:05,320 --> 02:32:10,538
Is that what you take pride in?
{\ O (spread)}

2152
02:32:10,538 --> 02:32:15,755
If you want to preach, then fight
with your pride on the line!
{\ O (spread)}

2153
02:32:15,755 --> 02:32:20,973
You can lecture me after you win!
{\ O (spread)}

2154
02:32:20,973 --> 02:32:26,190
<i>Now’s the time, to let
courage resonate in my heart</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2155
02:32:26,190 --> 02:32:31,407
<i>I’m not scared of pain</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2156
02:32:31,407 --> 02:32:36,625
<i>I must find the strength to stand up</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2157
02:32:36,625 --> 02:32:41,842
<i>Tomorrow, tomorrow, tomorrow,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2158
02:32:47,060 --> 02:32:49,060
<i>Tomorrow is right now!</i>
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Tomorrow for sure}

2159
02:32:49,060 --> 02:32:52,660
Old man!
{\ O (spread)}

2160
02:32:52,660 --> 02:32:56,260
Melt!
{\ O (spread)}

2161
02:32:56,260 --> 02:32:59,859
I didn’t follow you to
become a hindrance!
{\ O (spread)}

2162
02:32:59,859 --> 02:33:03,460
Speedwagon...
{\ O (spread)}

2163
02:33:03,460 --> 02:33:07,060
<i>I’ll let courage resonate in my heart</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2164
02:33:07,060 --> 02:33:10,660
<i>And look the enemy in the eyes</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2165
02:33:10,660 --> 02:33:14,260
<i>Won’t wait for a distant tomorrow</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2166
02:33:14,260 --> 02:33:17,859
<i>I’ll start walking,</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2167
02:33:17,859 --> 02:33:21,460
<i>Find the strength to
get back on my feet</i>
{\ O (spread)}

2168
02:33:25,060 --> 02:33:27,060
<i>Tomorrow is now!</i>
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Tomorrow and now}

2169
02:33:27,060 --> 02:33:34,878
JoJo!
{\ O (spread)}

2170
02:33:34,878 --> 02:33:42,696
Cut finely, beat of my blood!
{\ O (spread)}

2171
02:33:42,696 --> 02:33:50,514
Please... This knight’s proud heart,
{\ O (spread)}

2172
02:33:50,514 --> 02:33:58,332
Let it somehow be restored!
{\ O (spread)}

2173
02:33:58,332 --> 02:34:06,150
I am the Dark Knight Bruford!
{\ O (spread)}

2174
02:34:06,150 --> 02:34:13,969
This pain means nothing to me!
{\ O (spread)}

2175
02:34:13,969 --> 02:34:21,787
Why aren’t you moving?
{\ O (spread)}

2176
02:34:21,787 --> 02:34:29,605
Just now,
{\ O (spread)}

2177
02:34:29,605 --> 02:34:37,423
You said “pain”.
{\ O (spread)}

2178
02:34:37,423 --> 02:34:45,241
That means that now,
{\ O (spread)}

2179
02:34:39,060 --> 02:34:41,060
Pain?
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: pain}

2180
02:34:41,060 --> 02:34:50,529
That’s why...
{\ O (spread)}

2181
02:34:53,060 --> 02:34:55,060
You can feel pain!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: You are feeling pain now}

2182
02:34:57,060 --> 02:34:59,060
Pain...
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: pain}

2183
02:35:00,000 --> 02:35:07,000
I stopped fighting you.
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: So I stopped fighting with you}

2184
02:35:07,000 --> 02:35:12,000
That’s why you stopped your sword.
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: So you stopped the sword}

2185
02:35:12,000 --> 02:35:15,000
You are a great knight.
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: You are a proud knight}

2186
02:35:15,000 --> 02:35:19,000
You are human!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Human}

2187
02:35:22,000 --> 02:35:26,000
Is proof of life!
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: Proof of Life}

2188
02:35:26,000 --> 02:35:29,500
So this is what it means to be human?
{\ O (spread)}

2189
02:35:33,000 --> 02:35:37,000
Because of this pain, I can also feel
the joy of being alive in this moment.
{\ O (rank)}
{\ T: I can feel the joy of being here now}

2190
02:35:45,000 --> 02:35:48,000
I feel a bizarre sense of peace now.
{\ O (rank)}
